notesStmt.note: Pencilled notes on f. 2v-3r are in Henry Charles Lea's hand.

msContents.summary: Works in two different hands bound together. The first is Niccoló Capasso's Ragionamenti in Latin written in one hand on various sizes of paper, with extensive marginal notes in the same hand (see also UPenn. Ms. Codex 588 and Ms. Codex 589, both in Italian). Contents of the Dissertationes jurisdictionales anonimae, written in a second hand are listed (index on f. 112).
